  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legally, it typically involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary between jurisdictions, but most include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origins of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming illegal funds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Attempting to disguise the source of criminal income\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide illegal funds\n\nPenalties often include:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential prison sentences\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional/business restrictions\n\nDifferent countries have specific legal frameworks, but most follow similar core principles established by international anti-money laundering standards.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
